<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="miss-v">miss <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /mɪs/    美 /mɪs/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>未击中；未得到；错过：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I hit the ball, but missed it.
我击球，但未击中。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She threw a plate at him angrily and only <strong>narrowly missed</strong>. 
她生气地朝他扔出一个盘子，差一点打中他。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>未看到；未听到；未察觉；未领会：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Having been asked to work overtime that evening, I missed a wonderful film. 
那天晚上我被要求加班，因此错过了一场精彩的电影。</p><footer>2012 重庆</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s a huge hotel on the corner. <strong>You can’t miss it</strong>. 
它在拐角处，是个大酒店。你不会找不到的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You are <strong>missing the point</strong> of what I’m saying. 
你们没有明白我的意思。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>未出席；未赶上：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Because of this injury, I had to miss school for a week. 
因为这个伤，我只好缺课一周。</p><footer>外研② – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We have <strong>missed the bus</strong>, so we’ll have to walk.
我们没赶上公交车，只得步行。</p></div>

<h4 id="4-escape">4.★ <strong>避开；躲开 (不好的事) (escape)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She jumped back just in time to miss being hit by a speeding car. 
她幸亏及时向后一跳，否则就被超速行驶的车撞到。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.<strong>发觉遗失；感到…不在：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She missed her watch on the way to work.
她在上班的路上把表弄丢了。</p></div>

<h4 id="6">6.★ <strong>想念；怀念；留恋：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I still miss the days when she was with us. 
我仍然怀念她和我们在一起的日子。</p><footer> 2010 全国</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="miss-out">miss out</h3>
<p>1.<strong>遗漏；失去 (机会)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ll read through the guest list again to make sure I haven’t missed anybody out. 
我要再看一遍宾客名单，以免漏掉谁。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Some children miss out because their parents worry about the safety of school trips.
一些孩子由于父母担心学校组织的旅行的安全问题而失去了参加的机会。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Cecily, I shall <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (想念) our pleasant talks when you leave.  （2015 陕西）  </li>
<li>We <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (未赶上) the last bus and didn’t have any money for taxi, so we had to walk home.  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. miss  2. missed  </p></div>